Given the function $f(x)=\ln x+ \frac {1}{2}ax^{2}-x-m$ ($m\in\mathbb{Z}$).  
(I) If $f(x)$ is an increasing function, find the range of values for $a$;  
(II) If $a < 0$, and $f(x) < 0$ always holds, find the minimum value of $m$.
